  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/sap-builders-blog-posts/how-to-scrape-images-from-google/bc-p/13942136#M369</id>
    <title>Re: How to scrape images from Google</title>
    <updated>2024-11-19T12:43:45.174000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;One thing I forgot to mention. When you are recording your screen, for example with a search term "cat", the automation will set the criteria for recognizes the screen by the word "cat" being in the title.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1732016602618.png" style="width: 233px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/192874iC8805504A0C44F18/image-dimensions/233x207/is-moderation-mode/true?v=v2" width="233" height="207" role="button" title="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1732016602618.png" alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1732016602618.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;You have to change his, for example, to contains "Google Search".&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/sap-builders-blog-posts/how-to-scrape-images-from-google/bc-p/13942136#M369"/>
    <published>2024-11-19T12:43:45.174000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/sap-builders-blog-posts/how-to-scrape-images-from-google/bc-p/13942164#M370</id>
    <title>Re: How to scrape images from Google</title>
    <updated>2024-11-19T12:57:13.488000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;And if you want to get larger images, you can define a new screen for when selecting one of the images.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1732016703300.png" style="width: 754px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/192876i168221D4529030C3/image-dimensions/754x379?v=v2" width="754" height="379" role="button" title="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1732016703300.png" alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1732016703300.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;The criteria for that picture I used was its class.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Then I retrieve its src property and use the Download File activity. All very simple.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1732018541109.png" style="width: 661px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/192895i20208AA0AF6A0555/image-dimensions/661x565/is-moderation-mode/true?v=v2" width="661" height="565" role="button" title="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1732018541109.png" alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1732018541109.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/sap-builders-blog-posts/how-to-scrape-images-from-google/bc-p/13942164#M370"/>
    <published>2024-11-19T12:57:13.488000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
